summary:
The Avengers when they realize they’re falling for someone:
Bruce Banner: ....Imma just hop onto this spaceship to nowhere real...
body:
The Avengers when they realize they’re falling for someone:

Bruce Banner: ….Imma just hop onto this spaceship to nowhere real quick

Natasha Romanoff: *seduce*

Thor: I am the mighty - oh fuck.

Loki: What is this icky thing happening inside of me? Is it….feelings? Quick, somebody stab me and get it out

Steve Rogers: Finally it is happening to meee

Clint Barton: I love you and how do you feel about spending the rest of your life on a farm in the middle if nowhere unconnected to the outside world where I can visit you when I’m not on deadly missions

Nick Fury: [probably same as Barton]

Phil Coulson: … I just want to say, ma’am, I am quite taken with you and if you do not have any prior engagements, I wonder if you would maybe consider … uhh.. this just in alien invasion in NYC I gotta go see ya

Peter Parker: Uhh umm.. well… s-see th-the thing is… oh crap

Stephen Strange: [showing off something spectacular he did]

Tony Stark: I mean I like that person but not like like, if you know what I mean, they’re ok - h-hey where do you think you’re going .. what do you mean you have stuff to do take me with you

body:
Regarding the AVAC Shutdown

To anyone who’s invested real money into the game and now feels scammed since the game will be rendered completely unplayable after the shutdown; the best revenge strategy I can recommend is to boycott all of Jam City’s future projects out of spite, especially since the company seems to be trying to promote Hogwarts Mystery as part of the shutdown.

And to anyone looking for a game to fill the void that Avengers Academy will leave behind, while I don’t know of any games that fit the same niche, there is a game that I do enjoy called the Alchemist Code, it’s got captivating storylines, easy to master mechanics and some of its special events involve crossovers with things like Final Fantasy XV, Fate/Stay Night and most recently Full Metal Alchemist.
